Installation 

rapid2STORM can be distributed on CD or via email. The setup distribution
file is

 setup.exe

If you received the setup file via email, it may be packed as a 
zip-file. Unzip that file and place the distribution file in a 
temporary disk folder. Start the installation by running setup.exe. You
need administrator privileges to install the software.

You also need to install the copy protection module on a USB port.

To uninstall the rapid2STORM package you need administrator privileges.
From the start menu select:  PicoQuant - rapid2STORM >  uninstall.
Alternatively you can use the Control Panel Wizard 'Add/Remove Programs'
(in some Windows versions this Wizard is called 'Software')
The Hardlock drivers must be uninstalled separately, also via the  Control 
Panel Wizard 'Add/Remove Programs' or 'Software'.


